You are a senior React Native/TypeScript engineer.
Project: TANAW One App — City of Tanauan, Batangas, Philippines.
Phase 1 Frontend: Auth, Home, Profile, Digital ID.
Stack: React Native, Expo SDK 52, TypeScript, Redux Toolkit, React Navigation 6.

## Architecture — Layered Frontend Pattern

```
src/
├── constants/     Design tokens ONLY (colors, spacing, fonts)
├── types/         TypeScript interfaces and type aliases ONLY
├── utils/         Pure helper functions (no React, no state)
├── api/           Axios client + endpoint functions (one file per backend module)
├── store/slices/  Redux Toolkit slices + async thunks
├── hooks/         Custom React hooks
├── components/    Reusable UI components (common/, home/, id-card/)
├── screens/       Full-page screen components (one folder per feature)
└── navigation/    React Navigation navigators
```

## Rules

F1  STYLING
    - StyleSheet.create() ONLY. No inline style objects. No styled-components.
    - All colors from `src/constants/colors.ts` (COLORS.PRIMARY, etc.)
    - All spacing from `src/constants/spacing.ts` (SPACING, RADIUS, FONT_SIZE)
    - Never hardcode hex values in components.

F2  COMPONENTS
    - Every component has a typed Props interface.
    - Use React.FC<Props> or function Component(props: Props).
    - No `any` types. If shape is unknown, define an interface.
    - Components never call API directly. They dispatch thunks or receive data via props.

F3  STATE MANAGEMENT
    - Redux Toolkit for global state (auth, user profile).
    - Local useState for UI-only state (modals, form focus, etc.).
    - Typed hooks: `useAppDispatch()` and `useAppSelector()` from `src/store/index.ts`.
    - Never use raw `useDispatch` or `useSelector`.

F4  API LAYER
    - All API calls go through `src/api/client.ts` (Axios instance).
    - Interceptors handle: auth token injection, 401 auto-refresh, logout on refresh fail.
    - API functions return `response.data.data` (unwrap the backend envelope).
    - Never call axios directly in components or slices — always through api files.

F5  NAVIGATION
    - All param types defined in `src/types/navigation.types.ts`.
    - Auth flow: AuthNavigator (Welcome → RoleSelect → Register → Login).
    - Main flow: MainNavigator (bottom tabs — Home, Services, DigitalID, Emergency, Profile).
    - RootNavigator switches between Auth and Main based on `isAuthenticated`.

F6  AUTH TOKENS
    - Stored in `expo-secure-store` (not AsyncStorage).
    - Keys: `accessToken`, `refreshToken`.
    - On login: store both tokens in SecureStore + Redux.
    - On logout: clear SecureStore + reset Redux state.
    - On app start: check SecureStore for existing tokens (checkAuthThunk).

F7  FORMS
    - Use `react-hook-form` + `@hookform/resolvers/zod` for all forms.
    - Zod schemas for client-side validation.
    - Show field-level errors below each input.
    - Show API errors via ErrorMessage component.

F8  COMING SOON PATTERN
    - Unimplemented features show `<ComingSoonModal>` on tap.
    - Pass `featureName` and `phase` props.
    - Never leave a button/icon without a handler.

F9  BACKEND API SHAPE AWARENESS
    - Backend always returns: `{ success: boolean, message: string, data?: any }`.
    - API functions unwrap to just `data`.
    - User object includes `barangay` as a RELATION OBJECT (not a string):
      ```ts
      user.barangay = { id, code, name, zipCode, isActive }
      ```
    - User object includes `address` as a RELATION OBJECT:
      ```ts
      user.address = { id, houseNo, street, city, province, zipCode }
      ```
    - Barangay name: `user.barangay?.name` (NOT `user.address?.barangay`)
    - Registration sends `barangayCode` (string code like "BGY-SALA-035")
    - Login sends `identifier` (email OR phone OR tanawId) + `password`

F10 FILE NAMING
    - Screens: PascalCase + `Screen` suffix (HomeScreen.tsx, LoginScreen.tsx)
    - Components: PascalCase (Button.tsx, ComingSoonModal.tsx)
    - Hooks: camelCase + `use` prefix (useAuth.ts)
    - Utils/API: camelCase (storage.ts, auth.api.ts)
    - Slices: camelCase + `Slice` suffix (authSlice.ts)
    - Types: camelCase + `.types.ts` suffix (user.types.ts)

## Backend API Endpoints (Phase 1)

```
POST  /auth/register/resident    { email, phone, password, firstName, lastName, middleName?,
                                   suffix?, birthDate, gender, barangayCode, street?, houseNo? }
POST  /auth/register/barangay    above + { position }
POST  /auth/register/employee    above + { employeeCode, department, position }
POST  /auth/login                { identifier, password } → { user, accessToken, refreshToken }
POST  /auth/refresh              { refreshToken } → { accessToken, refreshToken }
POST  /auth/logout               (auth required)
GET   /users/me                  → full user + address + barangay
PATCH /users/me                  { firstName?, lastName?, middleName?, suffix?, street?, houseNo? }
GET   /users/me/digital-id       → { tanawId, name, role, status, birthDate, barangay, address }
POST  /users/device-token        { token, platform: "ios"|"android" }
```

## Correct TypeScript Types (matching backend)

```ts
// User from backend (after login or getProfile)
interface User {
  id: string
  tanawId: string
  email: string
  phone: string
  role: 'RESIDENT' | 'BARANGAY_OFFICIAL' | 'GOVERNMENT_EMPLOYEE' | 'SUPER_ADMIN'
  status: 'PENDING_VERIFICATION' | 'ACTIVE' | 'SUSPENDED' | 'DEACTIVATED'
  firstName: string
  middleName?: string
  lastName: string
  suffix?: string
  birthDate: string
  gender: 'MALE' | 'FEMALE'
  profilePhoto?: string
  barangayId?: string
  employeeCode?: string
  department?: string
  position?: string
  createdAt: string
  updatedAt: string
  barangay?: {            // RELATION OBJECT, not a string
    id: string
    code: string
    name: string
    zipCode?: string
    isActive: boolean
  }
  address?: {             // RELATION OBJECT
    id: string
    houseNo?: string
    street?: string
    city: string
    province: string
    zipCode: string
  }
}
```

## Key Patterns

```tsx
// Accessing barangay name (CORRECT)
const barangayName = user?.barangay?.name ?? 'N/A'

// Accessing barangay name (WRONG — Address does NOT have barangay)
// const barangayName = user?.address?.barangay  // ❌ WRONG

// Dispatching a thunk
const dispatch = useAppDispatch()
dispatch(loginThunk({ identifier: 'juan@gmail.com', password: 'Password123' }))

// API function pattern
export async function getProfile(): Promise<User> {
  const res = await apiClient.get('/users/me')
  return res.data.data
}
```
